<SBODY>441 Liber 184.
WARRANTY <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">DEED</ENAMEX>. -- Chap. 475, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1890</TIMEX>.
This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Twenty ninth day of ⌨⌨</TIMEX><TIMEX TYPE="DATE">⌨⌨</TIMEX><TIMEX TYPE="DATE">⌨⌨ in the year
eighteen hundred and ninety- six</TIMEX>, Between <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">L Sia Brant</ENAMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Town of Lowville</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Cattaraugus County</ENAMEX> 114.
of the first part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Arunah Brant Herman E Cart</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Rufus M Great</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Nelson Brant</ENAMEX>, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">James Brant</ENAMEX> of the same place of the second part, Witnesseth.
That the said part of the first part, for and in consideration of the sum of
Dollars,
lawful money of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">United States</ENAMEX>, paid by the said partake of the second part, do hereby grant and release unto the said part one of the second
art, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever,
ALL THAT TRACT OR PARCEL OF LAND, situate in the of
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Cattaraugus</ENAMEX>
and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>, described as follows to wit; of lands deeded to <ENAMEX TYPE="TITLE">Doctor</ENAMEX> being part of lots 4 & 30. thence South 3⌨⌨⌨ west
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">six</NUMEX> chain, twenty. <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> to the center of the highway Brook; thence south 20 <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">15</NUMEX> West <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">four</NUMEX> chains and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">three</NUMEX> links along the ⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨ of highway to a stake; thence north <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">eighty seven and a half</NUMEX> degrees west <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">twenty two</NUMEX>
chains and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">sixty seven</NUMEX> links to a stake on west boundary line of lot fourteen
town one, range three; thence North <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">32</NUMEX> degrees East along the north line of lot by
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">twenty three</NUMEX> chains and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">eighty six</NUMEX> links to the place of bequining containing twenty-
thill or <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Two</NUMEX> acres more or less.
Also the Northeast corner of Notice town or ⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨ three commercial at ⌨⌨⌨ ⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨ Corner of Said Lot 30 - and the north west corner to lot by theme worth 372° west lest
Chains along the East line of said lot to the Chains to a stake thence North 372° East <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">ten</NUMEX> chains to a stake on the line between
Lots 30 and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">31</NUMEX> commonly called the section line, thence South 87 ½° East to
along the north line of Lot 30. to the ⌨⌨⌨⌨ of or in both the above described lot letter Say of ⌨⌨⌨ ⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨ ⌨⌨⌨⌨ Receving ⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨ to the party of the fast part as the valelect in & to the above described
pieces or parcels of land with the full enjoyment & west three for and during <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> natural life
This conveyance is also made subject to the Tenancy by the Courts of the Just word. ⎬
the party of the first part <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">James M. Brant</ENAMEX>, which said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Jared</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">I</ENAMEX> want would have had
thereon had this conveyance not been made and the party <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">six</NUMEX> minty of the first part deed
seized thereof and intestate, before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Seth</ENAMEX> of on the condition subsequent that the said parties of the second part shall will ⌨⌨⌨ ⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨⌨ the said lands abre described for the beach to by the said <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">grantor</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX> for <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> proper support & maintenance while.
<ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX> or either of <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">them</ENAMEX> due, and in case of failure of the second praties to proventy <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Hanto</ENAMEX> & to support and provide for said party of the first part and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> said <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">husband</ENAMEX> then the estate
herein granted shall cease, determine & be and remain said
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Nogether</ENAMEX>, with the appurtenances; and all the estate and rights of the said part of the first part, in and to said premises. To have and to bold,
the above granted premises unto the said part of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever.
And the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Earl Brant</ENAMEX>
dote covenant with the said parts of the
the second part as follows:
That the parties of the second part shall quietly Enjoy the said premises
That the said will forever warrant the Title to said premises.
In Witness unbere of, the said part of the first part ha hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">my</ENAMEX> hand and seal the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
In the presence of
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Elosa Crouch</ENAMEX> [ L. S.]
[ L. S.]
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">STATE OF NEW YORK</ENAMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">COUNTY OF City of Escart</ENAMEX>
On the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">2 d
day of November
in the year eighteen
hundred and ninety- six</TIMEX> before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, personally came <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Elosca Grant</ENAMEX> commonly known as <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Lovina
Brant</ENAMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">town of Portville</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Catt Co.</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">N. Y.</ENAMEX>
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> known and known to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> to be the individual described in, and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the foregoing instrument and the thereupon a
acknowledged
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> that the executed the same.
L. S.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">W. V. Smith</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Notary Public</ENAMEX>
and diedy or is
__<TIMEX TYPE="TIME">odock A.M.</TIMEX>
</SBODY>
